statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from (select count(orders.id) as total_order, tem_order_details.total_sold_qty, tem_order_details.total_buying_price, tem_order_details.total_selling_price, DATE_FORMAT(orders.order_date,'%d-%m-%y') as order_date from `orders` left join (SELECT order_id, sum(quantity) as total_sold_qty, sum(total_buying_price) as total_buying_price, sum(total_selling_price) as total_selling_price from `order_details` group by order_id ) tem_order_details  on `orders`.`id` = `tem_order_details`.`order_id` where `order_date` between '2022-06-01' and '2022-06-10' group by `orders`.`order_date`) as `aggregate_table`

select count(orders.id) as total_order, tem_order_details.total_sold_qty, tem_order_details.total_buying_price, tem_order_details.total_selling_price, DATE_FORMAT(orders.order_date,'%d-%m-%y') as order_date from `orders` left join (SELECT order_id, sum(quantity) as total_sold_qty, sum(total_buying_price) as total_buying_price, sum(total_selling_price) as total_selling_price from `order_details` group by order_id ) tem_order_details  on `orders`.`id` = `tem_order_details`.`order_id` where `order_date` between '2022-06-01' and '2022-06-10' group by `orders`.`order_date` limit 10 offset 0
